{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Pin down one-line pointer shape in AGENTS.md with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fa6009ba8bdf16b0c"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"one-line pointer shape in AGENTS.md"},{"coaching":"Plan how CONTRIBUTING.md coverage in AC4 verification script will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f144778d04ad0203d","f370c6642d36223e9"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"CONTRIBUTING.md coverage in AC4 verification script"},{"coaching":"Plan how dangling-pointer check for repo-root files will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f370c6642d36223e9"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"dangling-pointer check for repo-root files"},{"coaching":"Run a quick pre-mortem on downstream breakage from CLAUDE.md reduction: how could this plan fail?","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f6e9299b87597432a","fa90bd3de2cd0cccd"],"move_id":"3","move_name":"pre-mortem","subject":"downstream breakage from CLAUDE.md reduction"},{"coaching":"State the concrete attestation evidence the [operator-attested] S1 delivery guarantee for ticket-model.md will require (a change id / vote outcome / timestamp), recorded on the ticket.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f0bbed4a92eca6719"],"move_id":"14","move_name":"state attestation evidence","subject":"S1 delivery guarantee for ticket-model.md"},{"coaching":"State the concrete attestation evidence the [operator-attested] native AGENTS.md support across named agents will require (a change id / vote outcome / timestamp), recorded on the ticket.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f080c22f0b7bf9716"],"move_id":"14","move_name":"state attestation evidence","subject":"native AGENTS.md support across named agents"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":9,"blocking":0,"dropped":7,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","probed":9,"ran":true,"references":9,"resolved":8,"status":"pass","unresolved_or_abstained":1},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":3889,"file_impact":2,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":0,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"pass","verify_commands_linted":46,"verify_lint_abstained":46},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":995,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P9":{"applicable":true,"blocking":false,"file_impact":2,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":224.4,"llm_calls":29,"llm_ms":406983.9,"total_ms":407308.5,"verify_requests":19},"remediation":{"baseline":"sidecar","eligible":false,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":false,"plan_changed":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"sidecar_baseline":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["A1","E4","G1G2","G6","G7","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8","removal-rationale"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","E5","E6","F1","G5","T12","T2","T4","T5b","T5e","T6","T7","T9","hedge"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Strengthen AC3's proving command to assert that each pointer section is a single line, e.g. use `awk` or `rg` to count the number of lines in each section referencing a docs path, or add a structural check such as `rg -c 'docs/[A-Za-z0-9_-]+\\.md' AGENTS.md` and assert the count equals the expected number of pointer topics (one match per topic, confirming no topic appears in a longer inline block).","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6","F1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Proving command: `rg -n 'docs/plan-review-gate.md|docs/mcp-reference.md|docs/ticket-model.md|docs/concurrency.md|docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md|docs/llm-framework.md' AGENTS.md`","This command returns any line containing the path; it does not assert the line IS the pointer (i.e. that each matching section is exactly one line).","Verify-command defect taxonomy: fixture invalidity — the command does not actually exercise the 'one-line' claim."],"finding":"AC3's proving command (`rg -n 'docs/plan-review-gate.md|...'`) only checks that the doc paths are mentioned *somewhere* in AGENTS.md, not that each documented topic appears as a *one-line pointer* rather than a restated multi-line section. A file that restates a section in full and also contains a passing `docs/…md` reference would satisfy the command while violating the AC.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa6009ba8bdf16b0c","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC3 ('Each already-documented topic is a one-line pointer, not a restated section.')","norm_id":"n3560d73c85d2c45b","priority":0.4813,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An executor writes a condensed 10-line summary of `docs/concurrency.md` content and appends 'See docs/concurrency.md for details.' The rg command passes; the AC is violated.","A reviewer running only the prescribed commands signs off on a file that still contains restated sections."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Replace or augment the current proving command with: `for doc in docs/plan-review-gate.md docs/mcp-reference.md docs/ticket-model.md docs/concurrency.md docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md docs/llm-framework.md; do count=$(rg -c \"$doc\" AGENTS.md); [ \"$count\" -eq 1 ] || { echo \"MULTI-LINE or MISSING pointer for $doc: $count lines\"; exit 1; }; done` — this asserts each doc is referenced exactly once (one pointer line), not multiple times across a restated section.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Extend AC #4's existence-check to also verify `CONTRIBUTING.md` (or any non-`docs/` pointer referenced by AGENTS.md), or add a separate AC confirming `CONTRIBUTING.md` exists before merging.","cohort":["COH","E1","T4"],"criteria":["E1","COH"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC #2: 'defers the full recipe to `CONTRIBUTING.md`'","AC #4 script: `rg -o 'docs/[A-Za-z0-9_-]+\\.md' AGENTS.md` — regex anchored to docs/ prefix, misses repo-root files","Design decisions: 'defers the full recipe to CONTRIBUTING.md (verbatim Gerrit → ~215-230, which misses the target)'"],"finding":"AC #4's verification script (`rg -o 'docs/[A-Za-z0-9_-]+\\.md' AGENTS.md`) only matches paths under `docs/`; it does not check `CONTRIBUTING.md` (repo root). The plan explicitly describes deferring the full Git/Gerrit recipe to `CONTRIBUTING.md`, making it a pointer target, yet no criterion verifies this file actually exists — creating a potential dangling pointer that passes all ACs.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f144778d04ad0203d","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC #2 (Git/Gerrit defers to CONTRIBUTING.md) vs. AC #4 (dangling-pointer check regex)","norm_id":"n55f05e4e76bd4108","priority":0.3438,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["CONTRIBUTING.md does not exist at implementation time; AGENTS.md points to it; AC #4 passes (wrong regex) and reviewers miss the dangling pointer"],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Amend AC #4's shell script to: `for p in $(rg -o '(?:docs/[A-Za-z0-9_-]+\\.md|CONTRIBUTING\\.md)' AGENTS.md | sort -u); do test -f \"$p\" || { echo \"MISSING $p\"; exit 1; }; done` — or add an explicit prerequisite noting that `CONTRIBUTING.md` must already exist (similar to the S1 dependency note for docs/ticket-model.md).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Extend AC4's proving command to also verify non-`docs/` file pointers (e.g. `CONTRIBUTING.md`) that AGENTS.md is required to cite, so the no-dangling-pointer guarantee covers all referenced paths.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC4 proving command: `for p in $(rg -o 'docs/[A-Za-z0-9_-]+\\.md' AGENTS.md | sort -u); do test -f \"$p\" || { echo \"MISSING $p\"; exit 1; }; done`","AC2: 'defers the full recipe to `CONTRIBUTING.md`' — CONTRIBUTING.md is at the repo root, not under docs/","Design decisions: 'Git/Gerrit section is condensed … and defers the full recipe to CONTRIBUTING.md'","Cached plan-review finding (826763c807b65ce3a1e9.json): 'AC #4's verification script only matches paths under docs/; it does not check CONTRIBUTING.md'"],"finding":"AC4's dangling-pointer proving command only checks `docs/`-prefixed paths but the plan explicitly requires AGENTS.md to defer the full Git/Gerrit recipe to `CONTRIBUTING.md` (a repo-root file, not under `docs/`). The regex `rg -o 'docs/[A-Za-z0-9_-]+\\.md' AGENTS.md` will silently skip `CONTRIBUTING.md`, leaving its pointer unverified. If an implementer writes the wrong filename or path, AC4 would not catch it.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f370c6642d36223e9","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC4 proving command","norm_id":"na9c540515b6eda98","priority":0.3438,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Implementer writes `CONTRIBUTNG.md` (typo) in AGENTS.md — AC4 passes, but the pointer is dangling.","Future refactor moves CONTRIBUTING.md — AC4 never detects the break."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Append a separate check to the AC4 proof: `rg -q 'CONTRIBUTING.md' AGENTS.md && test -f CONTRIBUTING.md` — or widen the regex to `rg -o '[A-Za-z0-9_/.-]+\\.md' AGENTS.md` and filter to repo-relative paths.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a pre-flight step (e.g., `rg -rn 'CLAUDE\\.md' . --include='*.md'`) to enumerate all existing references to CLAUDE.md, then either update each caller to point at AGENTS.md or add a forwarding note in the new thin CLAUDE.md for any section heading that other docs cite.","cohort":["T2","T5e","T7"],"criteria":["T7"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["CLAUDE.md currently contains substantial content (Git/Gerrit, session-logs, library snippets, etc.); the plan removes all of it but does not include a step like `rg -r 'CLAUDE.md' .` to find and update callers.","The 'stowaway' topics are stated to be 'simply not carried into AGENTS.md' — no forwarding pointer or migration note is planned for content that is dropped rather than moved.","AC lines verify AGENTS.md and CLAUDE.md content but contain no check for external references to CLAUDE.md sections."],"finding":"The plan does not audit whether existing files (READMEs, other docs, CI configs, or onboarding materials) currently reference CLAUDE.md by name or section heading; reducing CLAUDE.md to a thin shim will strand those references without warning.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6e9299b87597432a","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section / 'In: new AGENTS.md, rewritten CLAUDE.md'","norm_id":"n20cfffabea04d960","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A contributing doc or README says 'see CLAUDE.md for Git workflow' — after the rewrite that section is gone and the link is dead.","An onboarding script or CI comment references a CLAUDE.md heading anchor that no longer exists."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add one AC: `rg -rn 'CLAUDE\\.md' . --include='*.md' | grep -v '^CLAUDE.md'` returns no results referencing removed section anchors; OR add a `## Moved` comment block at the top of the new thin CLAUDE.md listing the old headings and their new locations.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.75,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Confirm that `docs/ticket-model.md` actually exists (i.e. S1 has merged) before this story is claimed, OR add an explicit gate/pre-condition check in the Scope/AC text that blocks implementation until S1's output is in `HEAD`.","cohort":["E4"],"criteria":["E4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["docs/ directory listing confirms ticket-model.md is absent: the file does not exist in the current tree.","Plan quote: 'targets created by S1 are in place by then' — forward-looking premise, not a verified current state.","AC#4 proving command: 'for p in $(rg -o docs/[A-Za-z0-9_-]+\\.md AGENTS.md | sort -u); do test -f \"$p\" || { echo \"MISSING $p\"; exit 1; }; done' — would fail on docs/ticket-model.md today.","G-4 scope-exclusion sub-check: the exclusion 'docs/ticket-model.md — created by S1' is an empirically checkable codebase claim that the tools refute in the current state."],"finding":"docs/ticket-model.md does not currently exist in the repository, but the plan's AC#4 proving script and the POINTER list both treat it as a real pointer target, relying entirely on an unverified S1 dependency claim ('targets created by S1 are in place by then'). The AC script `test -f \"$p\" || exit 1` will fail for this path if run before S1 lands, and there is no guard in the AC or Scope text confirming S1 has already merged.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f0bbed4a92eca6719","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section ('Depends on S1'); AC#4 ('Every docs/…md path that AGENTS.md points at resolves to a real file'); What section ('ticket model → docs/ticket-model.md (created by S1)')","norm_id":"ne8669600187f0e38","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["If this story is implemented before S1 merges, AGENTS.md will contain a dangling pointer to docs/ticket-model.md and AC#4's shell proving command will exit 1.","If a reviewer or CI runs the AC verification shell script after this story lands but before S1 lands, the gate fails with no obvious cause."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add to the Scope section: 'Prerequisite check: `test -f docs/ticket-model.md || { echo \"S1 not yet merged — do not implement this story\"; exit 1; }` must pass before work begins.' This makes the S1 dependency machine-verifiable rather than relying on prose.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7778,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Enumerate and address all files outside the edit set that reference `CLAUDE.md` by name or section anchor (including `README.md:354`, `CONTRIBUTING.md:570`, `docs/architecture.md:65`, `docs/releasing.md:250`, `docs/api-stability.md:25`, `docs/llm-framework.md:462`, `docs/workflow-editor.md:160`, `docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md:467`, `rebar.toml:3`, `docs/adr/0043-operator-attested-completion-evidence.md:121`) — either update them to point at the new target locations in AGENTS.md/docs/, or explicitly scope the sweep to a sibling story.","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["CONTRIBUTING.md:570: 'see `CLAUDE.md`'","docs/architecture.md:65: 'see CLAUDE.md \"Session logs\"' — section being dropped/moved","docs/releasing.md:250: 'see \"Git workflow\" in CLAUDE.md /'","docs/api-stability.md:25: '[CLAUDE.md](../CLAUDE.md)' linking to the MCP tool set section","docs/llm-framework.md:462: 'See CLAUDE.md\\'s \"Ticket template the gates enforce\" section.'","docs/workflow-editor.md:160: reference to 'the repo-root `CLAUDE.md`'","README.md:354: '[CLAUDE.md](CLAUDE.md#ticket-template-the-gates-enforce)' — anchor will not exist in 30-line file","docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md:467: 'ADR / CLAUDE.md / design-doc update'","rebar.toml:3: '# See docs/llm-framework.md and CLAUDE.md for the close gate + LLM module.'","docs/adr/0043-operator-attested-completion-evidence.md:121: 'CLAUDE.md authoring note'"],"finding":"At least 13 files OUTSIDE the plan's edit set (new AGENTS.md + rewritten CLAUDE.md) contain hard references to CLAUDE.md by name, including section-specific anchors and prose pointers to named sections that will no longer exist after CLAUDE.md is reduced to ≤30 lines. None of these consumers are enumerated or addressed by the plan.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa90bd3de2cd0cccd","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section ('In: new AGENTS.md, rewritten CLAUDE.md. No writes to any docs/* file'); unenumerated consumers","norm_id":"n9624b9b10bf53838","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["README.md:354 links to CLAUDE.md#ticket-template-the-gates-enforce, an anchor that will not exist in the 30-line reduced file — broken link.","docs/llm-framework.md:462 tells readers 'See CLAUDE.md\\'s \"Ticket template the gates enforce\" section' — section is gone, readers find a one-line @AGENTS.md import instead.","docs/architecture.md:65 points to CLAUDE.md \"Session logs\" — section removed, readers hit empty pointer."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a sub-step (or a sibling story dependency) that: (1) runs `rg -rn 'CLAUDE\\.md' --include='*.md' --include='*.toml' --include='*.py' . | grep -v '^CLAUDE.md'` to enumerate all consumers, (2) updates section-specific anchors (e.g. `CLAUDE.md#ticket-template-the-gates-enforce` → `AGENTS.md#ticket-template-the-gates-enforce` or the appropriate docs/ pointer), and (3) adds a verify command that asserts no file outside CLAUDE.md itself contains a broken anchor reference to CLAUDE.md sections.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Verify and cite documentation (or a spike result) confirming that each of the 11 named tools reads `AGENTS.md` natively at launch — or narrow the list to those that can be confirmed, noting which require additional per-tool config (as already documented in `docs/session-id-shims.md` for Codex and Cursor).","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan quote: 'AGENTS.md is read natively by Codex, Cursor, Copilot's coding agent, Zed, Windsurf, Amp, Factory, Jules, Devin, RooCode, and Cline'","docs/session-id-shims.md lines 77-101: Codex config mechanism is config.toml with shell_environment_policy.set — no mention of AGENTS.md","docs/session-id-shims.md lines 102-128: Cursor uses environment.json install script + Secrets tab — no mention of AGENTS.md","No file in the repo links to documentation confirming AGENTS.md native support for Windsurf, Amp, Factory, Jules, Devin, RooCode, or Cline","ABSENCE: No prior-art or capability-verification evidence is cited in the plan for any of the 11 tools beyond the Claude Code @-import spike"],"finding":"The plan asserts 'AGENTS.md is read natively by Codex, Cursor, Copilot's coding agent, Zed, Windsurf, Amp, Factory, Jules, Devin, RooCode, and Cline' as a given fact, but provides no linked documentation or prior-art evidence for the majority of these tools. The repo's own session-id-shims.md — which directly investigates per-tool config surfaces — shows Codex uses config.toml (not AGENTS.md) and Cursor uses environment.json/Secrets, which are inconsistent with the blanket 'natively reads AGENTS.md' claim for those tools.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f080c22f0b7bf9716","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Why section: 'AGENTS.md is read natively by Codex, Cursor, Copilot's coding agent, Zed, Windsurf, Amp, Factory, Jules, Devin, RooCode, and Cline'","norm_id":"n1f26cde69d8c9016","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["If several of these tools don't actually read AGENTS.md natively (e.g. they look for tool-specific files), the 'one canonical AGENTS.md covers the ecosystem' premise fails and the plan's core Why is overstated.","Future maintainers may rely on this list as authoritative and skip per-tool shim setup, causing guidance to silently not load in some agents."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Replace the blanket claim with a table or footnote distinguishing confirmed native AGENTS.md readers (e.g. OpenAI Codex/Responses API, GitHub Copilot coding agent) from tools that use AGENTS.md via a configured path or do not support it natively (Cursor, Codex CLI via config.toml), with a doc link per tool.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Link a concrete evidence artifact (a public Anthropic docs URL, a commit to the Claude Code changelog, or a captured spike log) that confirms `@AGENTS.md` transclusion works in the Claude Code version this repo targets, and clarify what 'headless canary' means in this context.","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan quote: 'PROVEN in Claude Code 2.1.211 (headless canary + official docs recommend exactly @AGENTS.md + ## Claude Code)'","No file in the repo (searched all paths) contains a spike result, session log, or linked Anthropic docs URL for this behavior","docs/session-id-shims.md line 29: 'If a future Claude Code changes those names/mechanism, the shim simply no-ops' — the repo itself acknowledges version-instability in Claude Code's config surface, making version-pinned capability assertions load-bearing","ABSENCE: No URL to the claimed 'official docs' is present in the plan"],"finding":"The plan states the '@AGENTS.md import is PROVEN in Claude Code 2.1.211 (headless canary + official docs recommend exactly @AGENTS.md + ## Claude Code)' as a design decision, but no linked evidence artifact (test log, session transcript, doc URL) is provided anywhere in the plan or the repo. 'Headless canary' is an opaque internal reference with no definition or link.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"ffa359a1a5d43188f","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Design decisions section: 'The @AGENTS.md import is PROVEN in Claude Code 2.1.211 (headless canary + official docs recommend exactly @AGENTS.md + ## Claude Code); no symlink fallback.'","norm_id":"nd82d99427cdc7759","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["If @AGENTS.md import syntax was in a canary build but later removed or changed before GA, the CLAUDE.md thin-pointer approach breaks silently with no fallback.","A reviewer cannot independently verify the spike without a linked artifact, making this the single largest unresolved capability assertion in the plan."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a 'Spike evidence' subsection under Design decisions with: (1) the Anthropic docs URL confirming @-import syntax, (2) the Claude Code version range it applies to, and (3) a note on whether a fallback (e.g. keeping CLAUDE.md content as a secondary copy) is warranted until the feature is GA-stable.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.6667,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a link to the spike evidence (ticket, log, or quoted official-docs URL) that confirms `@AGENTS.md` bare-filename import resolves correctly in the Claude Code version used in this repo, and document the fallback behavior if import resolution fails.","cohort":["T3"],"criteria":["T3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'The `@AGENTS.md` import is PROVEN in Claude Code 2.1.211 (headless canary + official docs recommend exactly `@AGENTS.md` + `## Claude Code`); no symlink fallback.'","No spike ticket link, no quoted official-docs URL, no session log reference supplied in the plan.","AC5 only checks `rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md` and line count — it does not verify that Claude Code actually resolves the import at runtime.","Evidence class: Partially-verified (the `@file` import feature exists in Claude Code generally; the exact bare-filename form `@AGENTS.md` and its root-relative resolution are unverified from plan text alone)."],"finding":"The plan asserts `@AGENTS.md` import is 'PROVEN in Claude Code 2.1.211 (headless canary)' and explicitly adopts 'no symlink fallback,' but provides no linked spike artifact (no ticket, log, screenshot, or quoted official-docs URL). If the import syntax is wrong or version-specific behavior differs in the deployed Claude Code version, CLAUDE.md silently delivers no guide content to Claude Code agents — with no fallback path.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fcb9029da01d3df90","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Design decisions (spike-validated) section","norm_id":"n808806d37583eaf1","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Claude Code version in the deployed environment resolves `@AGENTS.md` relative to CWD rather than repo root, silently loading nothing.","The correct syntax is `@./AGENTS.md` or `@{repo_root}/AGENTS.md` in the deployed version, making the one-line CLAUDE.md a no-op.","A future Claude Code update changes the import mechanism; with no fallback, all Claude Code agents lose access to the guide."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In the Design decisions section, add a direct quote or URL from the Claude Code official docs confirming the `@AGENTS.md` syntax, and reference the spike ticket/log by id. Alternatively, add a one-line fallback comment in CLAUDE.md (e.g., pointing humans to `AGENTS.md` directly) so the file is not a pure black-box stub.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.6667,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a brief comment block (3–5 lines) inside the new `CLAUDE.md` itself, or a `docs/adr-agents-bridge.md`, explaining why CLAUDE.md is intentionally thin and that AGENTS.md is the canonical source — so the decision survives the ticket lifecycle.","cohort":["T2","T5e","T7"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'The @AGENTS.md import is PROVEN in Claude Code 2.1.211' — rationale lives in the plan, not in a lasting artifact.","After merge, a future contributor encountering the thin CLAUDE.md (@AGENTS.md + optional ## Claude Code) has no in-repo record of why this structure was chosen over alternatives (symlink, duplicate, etc.).","No ADR or docs/design-*.md file is listed in the Scope 'In' list."],"finding":"The novel architectural decision — AGENTS.md as the single canonical dev guide bridging all coding agents via @-import into CLAUDE.md — is captured only in the ephemeral plan ticket, not in a durable ADR or in-repo design note that survives after the ticket closes.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f8eeba3cabbf19459","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Design decisions section / Why section","norm_id":"n06e0373f42a42171","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A future maintainer sees the minimal CLAUDE.md, assumes it is incomplete, and restores duplicated content — re-introducing the anti-pattern this story fixes.","A new coding agent integration asks 'why is CLAUDE.md empty?' and there is no discoverable answer in the repo."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In the new CLAUDE.md, after `@AGENTS.md`, add a `## Why this file is short` section (≤5 lines) citing the ecosystem rationale and pointing to the Why section of the plan (or AGENTS.md intro). This keeps it within the ≤30 line AC and serves as a durable design note.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Name the two 'stowaway' topics in the What/Scope section by their actual heading or content description (e.g. 'the LLM agent-operations sub-section and the completion-verification close gate blurb within CLAUDE.md §Session logs') so an executor can identify and exclude them without ambiguity.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan quote: 'the two \"stowaway\" topics currently mixed into CLAUDE.md\\'s Session-logs heading are simply not carried into AGENTS.md'","CLAUDE.md Session logs section (lines 191–274) contains: (1) the session_log ticket-type specification (gate/lifecycle-exempt, visibility, non-blocking-links, Jira exclusion, title convention, capture helper, auto-rotation); (2) LLM agent operations (review_ticket, verify_completion, review_code, scan_spec); (3) the completion-verification close gate description — three distinct topic clusters, making 'two stowaway topics' ambiguous without a naming.","ABSENCE: The plan names no topic identifiers, section headings, or line ranges for the two topics to be omitted — the value vocabulary of the referenced set is entirely absent."],"finding":"The plan references 'the two stowaway topics currently mixed into CLAUDE.md's Session-logs heading are simply not carried into AGENTS.md' but never names or enumerates those two topics. An executor implementing AGENTS.md cannot determine which content to drop without knowing the membership of this referenced set.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fb59ce762daf4cf17","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — POINTER paragraph, final parenthetical: 'the two \"stowaway\" topics currently mixed into CLAUDE.md's Session-logs heading are simply not carried into AGENTS.md'","norm_id":"n0d83688f43ef0094","priority":0.1132,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An executor reads CLAUDE.md's Session logs section, sees three distinct sub-topics (session_log type spec, LLM agent ops, completion-verification gate), and cannot determine which two are the 'stowaway' topics to drop — different reasonable interpretations yield different AGENTS.md content.","The executor omits the wrong two topics (e.g. drops session_log spec instead of the LLM-ops sub-section), producing an AGENTS.md that misleads agents about session log behavior."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Replace the parenthetical with: 'the two stowaway topics — (1) the LLM agent-operations sub-section (review_ticket / verify_completion / scan_spec) and (2) the completion-verification close gate blurb — currently embedded under CLAUDE.md § Session logs are simply not carried into AGENTS.md (both are already covered by docs/llm-framework.md and docs/plan-review-gate.md respectively).'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.4286,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The described work of re-homing two stowaways (LLM-ops paragraph → `docs/llm-framework.md`; close-gate blockquote → `docs/plan-review-gate.md`) is a migration, but no AC verifies that the destination files exist and contain the moved content — only that AGENTS.md *points* to them. E1d requires verifying BOTH removal AND replacement for migrations.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4a0bbd3a940b188e","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC4 / 'Re-home two stowaways' in What section","norm_id":"ne8523bfe13fd302c","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add to Acceptance Criteria:\n```\n- [ ] `docs/llm-framework.md` exists and contains the LLM-agent-operations content.\n  Proving: `test -f docs/llm-framework.md && rg -q 'llm' docs/llm-framework.md`\n- [ ] `docs/plan-review-gate.md` contains the completion-verification close-gate content.\n  Proving: `rg -q 'close.gate\\|completion.verif' docs/plan-review-gate.md`\n```","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The Acceptance Criteria verify that AGENTS.md *points to* docs/llm-framework.md and docs/plan-review-gate.md, but no AC or proof checks that those target files actually *exist and contain the re-homed content*. If the stowaway target files do not exist, the pointers are broken and the re-homing goal is silently unfulfilled.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f72f715d0def1541f","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"## What — 'Re-home two stowaways' bullet; AC item 4 ('llm-framework.md present as a pointer')","norm_id":"n2bdf011401fc4df3","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add two AC items:\n```\n- [ ] docs/llm-framework.md exists and contains the LLM-agent-operations content.\n  Proving: `test -f docs/llm-framework.md && rg -l 'LLM.agent.operat' docs/llm-framework.md`\n- [ ] docs/plan-review-gate.md contains the completion-verification close-gate block.\n  Proving: `rg -n 'completion.verif' docs/plan-review-gate.md`\n```","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The AC proving commands verify that AGENTS.md *contains* pointer strings (e.g. `rg -n 'docs/ticket-model.md' AGENTS.md`) but no AC verifies that the pointer *target files actually exist*. Since `docs/ticket-model.md` does not currently exist in the repo and depends on a separate story (S1), an executor who runs this story before S1 completes will ship AGENTS.md with a broken link while all ACs pass green. The dependency is named in 'Scope' but is not enforced at the AC level.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f70b4fde83bc0ffce","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC3 proving command; Scope — 'Depends on S1'","norm_id":"n308261db195e7c59","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Extend AC3's proving command to include existence checks for files that may not yet exist: `test -f docs/ticket-model.md && rg -n 'docs/ticket-model.md' AGENTS.md`. Alternatively, add a standalone AC: 'All docs/ files pointed to by AGENTS.md exist. Proving: `for f in docs/plan-review-gate.md docs/mcp-reference.md docs/ticket-model.md docs/concurrency.md docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md docs/reuse-surface.md docs/event-schema.md docs/user-guide.md docs/llm-framework.md; do test -f \"$f\" || (echo \"MISSING: $f\" && exit 1); done`'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["COH","E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The Scope section defines deliverables as 'In: new AGENTS.md, rewritten CLAUDE.md' only, but the De-risking section adds two additional write operations — re-homing content to `docs/llm-framework.md` and `docs/plan-review-gate.md` — that are outside the stated scope. Neither the Scope nor the AC set has a criterion verifying these re-homing operations are complete, leaving them as uncovered work.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f626ab25b7748efc6","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section ('In: new AGENTS.md, rewritten CLAUDE.md') vs De-risking section ('Two stowaways ... must be RE-HOMED ... to docs/llm-framework.md / docs/plan-review-gate.md')","norm_id":"n24c376691fe37f35","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add to Scope 'In:': '`docs/llm-framework.md` (add LLM-agent-operations paragraph), `docs/plan-review-gate.md` (add completion-verification close-gate blockquote).' Add AC: '`docs/llm-framework.md` contains the LLM-agent-operations content and `docs/plan-review-gate.md` contains the completion-verification blockquote previously in CLAUDE.md.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The 'In:' scope list names only 'new AGENTS.md, rewritten CLAUDE.